
choice
    prompt "Core Binaries (sh, ls etc.)"
    default BUSYBOX

    config BUSYBOX
    bool "BusyBox"
    help
        BusyBox is an implementation of many Unix commands in a single executable file 

endchoice

config HTOP
    bool "HTOP"
    help
        Don't even bother, it does not run

config BASH
    bool "BASH"
    default y

config SUDO
    bool "sudo"
    default y
    help
        Well... its sudo...

config VIM
    bool "vim"
    default y
    help
        Vim is a greatly improved version of the good old UNIX editor Vi.

config X11
    bool "X Graphical System"
    default y
    help
        Build the X11 libraries and Xorg server. (aka the Graphical Interface)

config XTERM
    bool "Xterm"
    default y
    depends on X11
    help
        Trust me, you will need it.

config LEAFPAD
    bool "Leafpad"
    default y
    depends on X11
    help
        Leafpad is a simple GTK+ text editor that emphasizes simplicity.
        As development focuses on keeping weight down to a minimum, only the most essential features are
        implemented in the editor.Leafpad is simple to use, is easily compiled, requires few libraries, and starts up quickly. 

config PCMANFM
    bool "PcManFM"
    default y
    depends on X11
    help
        A classic file manager.

choice
    prompt "Window Manager"
    default ICEWM
    depends on X11

    config ICEWM
    bool "IceWM"
    help
        IceWM is a simple window manager that resembles windows 9x, has a start menu... and umm... its a window manager.
        It does run quite slower (At least moving/resizing) compared to twm

    config TWM
    bool "twm"
    help
        TWM is as simple as it gets. Its a window manager, runs very fast but it is very minimalistic.
        You will need a terminal.
endchoice
